Jeanette Chabalala, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Witbank &ndash; Police are searching for two inmates who escaped from the Witbank Correctional Centre on Thursday, the Department of Correctional Services said on Saturday.&nbsp;The department&rsquo;s spokesperson Manelisi Wolela said Mduduzi Johnson Khubheka and Vusimuzi Geraald Skosana wrestled with a female official and escaped through the main gate of the perimeter fence.&nbsp; He said the two drove off with another official&rsquo;s car, which was later found abandoned after it went into a ditch.&nbsp; The vehicle&rsquo;s key was still in the ignition and a cellphone was left in the vehicle, he said.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&ldquo;The public is advised to report any suspicion or information regarding the escapees to the police and not take the law into their own hands,&rdquo; said Wolela.&nbsp;&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.